[SN]TITLE[SN]
Biker dies and passenger hurt in Chilham crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A motorcyclist has died and his passenger is seriously injured in hospital after a crash with a car.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 49-year-old man from Rochester died at the scene on the A252 in Chilham, Kent, at 13:48 BST on Sunday.
His passenger, a 43-year-old woman from Gillingham, was taken to hospital with life-threatening injuries.
The driver of the Vauxhall Zafira involved suffered minor injuries. Police are appealing for any witnesses to the collision to come forward.
